HEADWORD: Canap
<hw>Ca`na`p⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
orig. a couch with mosquito curtains. See <er>Canopy</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A sofa or divan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>an appetizer consisting of a
thin slice or piece of bread toasted or fried in butter or oil, on which
anchovies, mushrooms, caviar, cheese, or other savory foods, are
served.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

